<TITLE> Stocks end up </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 15 (bdnews24.com)Markets ended upbeat on the opening day of the week as confident investors continued to bet on shares seeing a positive trend in the past two weeks, said observers. Turnover on the Dhaka Stock Exchange topped the Tk 600 crore mark Sunday for the second successive trading day. The prime bourse's turnover crept down to Tk 611.08 crore, with 39,285,149 shares trading hands, after hitting a new high of Tk 611.93 crore Thursday. Turnover on the Chittagong Stock Exchange rose to Tk 74.76 crore from Tk 70.31 crore on Thursday, with 7,892,822 shares traded. Market observers said the rise was anticipated as the market has been witnessing an upbeat trend for the last two weeks. "Investors, both retail and institutional, are putting money on scrips," Imtiaz Hossain, who runs a brokerage house, told bdnews24.com. Investors seemed "very optimistic" about long-term profits, reflected in rising stock prices and high turnover, he added. Economist Abu Ahmed said retail investors in particular were entering the market as it heated up. "This always happens in our market; people come in when they see prices are going up." "Companies are also declaring dividends right now," added Ahmed, an adviser to the Securities and Exchange Commission. The DSE witnessed a sharp rise in early trading, and remained more or less steady throughout the day. The DGEN or general index was up 18.27 points or 0.68 percent to finish at 2671.38. The DSI or all share price index ended on 2222.01, gaining 15.82 points or 0.71 percent. The bourse's blue-chip DSE-20, however, edged down 1.36 points or 0.63 percent to 2143.16. Of the traded issues, 143 gained, 107 lost and eight remained unchanged. Indices on the Chittagong Stock Exchange ended upbeat paced by gains in textile, pharmaceuticals and cement. The CSCX or selective categories index gained 53.03 points or one percent to close at 5327.77. The CASPI or all share price index ended on 8255.17, up by 82.46 points or one percent. The CSE-30 blue-chip index rose 46.88 points or 0.71 percent to close on 6564.65. Of the traded issues, 94 advanced, 83 declined with five scrips holding steady. DSE's top ten by turnover Sector heavyweight Summit Power continued to gain, closing at Tk 1025.50, up by 2.70 percent. Shinepukur Ceramics eroded the previous trading day's gains; it lost 1.50 percent to end on Tk 111.30. Beximco Pharmaceuticals crept up 0.06 percent to close at Tk 165.20. Beximco closed at Tk 196, up 1.29 percent. State owned Titas Gas rose 2.51 percent to Tk 488.50. Among the other scrips on the turnover board Summit Alliance Port Ltd, Square Pharmaceuticals, BSRSM Steel and Beximco Textiles also ended up. Profit-taking led S Alam Cold Rolled Steels to close down.
